  "title": "Settlement Officer (Bank Ops I East I Up to 5k)",
  "description": "<p><strong>The Opportunity</strong></p><ul><li>Opportunity to work for one of the leading financial service providers and top banks</li><li>Great exposure to learn about banking products and services domain</li><li>East Location</li></ul><p><br /><strong>The Job</strong></p><ul><li>Process external and internal asset transfers covering equities, fixed income, funds, and digital assets</li><li>Coordinate with CDP, Front Office, custodians, and external third parties to ensure smooth transfer and settlement</li><li>Investigate and resolve cash and securities breaks promptly</li><li>Ensure all transfer instructions comply with bank operating guidelines and market requirements</li><li>Handle security transfer queries from Front Office and other stakeholders</li><li>Support and lead ad‑hoc projects to enhance processes and systems</li><li>Work with project teams to ensure timely and accurate implementation</li><li>Perform additional duties assigned by the team</li><li>Provide operational support to the team leader when required</li></ul><p><strong>The Talent</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in Finance, Business, or related field</li><li>1-3 years of experience in securities settlement or asset transfers</li><li>Basic understanding of equities, bonds, and funds</li><li>Experience with CDP or market settlement processes is an advantage</li><li>Strong attention to detail and problem‑solving skills</li><li>Good communication skills and able to work independently</li></ul><p><strong>Next Steps</strong></p><ul><li>Send your resume to <strong>yueshan.wu@adecco.com</strong></li><li>Email Topic: Settlement Officer</li></ul><p><br /></p><p>Wu Yue Shan<br />EA License No: 91C2918<br />Personnel Registration Number: R25138923</p>",
